size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>While acknowledgi=
ng that the thought of being automated out of a job could be &#8220;frighte=
ning,&#8221; Asimov envisioned a world in which machines allow humans to be=
 more human. Instead of doing what we have to do to survive, humans might s=
pend their time like aristocrats of old, becoming &#8220;educated in litera=
ture, the arts, and philosophy.&#8221; Of course, people could choose impac=
