r lunar mining or any of the professions that would seem vital to the prope=
r functioning of the world,&#8221; but that would be entirely up to them. &=
#8220;Every field will be an elective, and the only guide will be &#8216;</=
span><strong>whatever you wish</strong><span>.&#8217;&#8221;&#160;</span></=
p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0=
 0 20px 0;"><span>As we hurtle towards that automated future, the question =
is: whose vision is more right, </span><strong>Vonnegut or Asimov?</strong>=
<span>&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-he=
ight: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>The general dialogue around automati=
on would suggest that Vonnegut&#8217;s is the more popularly held. I&#8217;=
ve written about the fear that </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redir=
ect/2def90c3-2d35-4b9a-a437-618fdc92e149?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_=
ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel=3D"" style=3D"color: #404040; text-de=
coration: underline;">robots will steal factory jobs</a><span>, despite evi=
dence to the contrary. Each recent advance in AI&#8217;s capabilities have =
been met with concerns about the economic prospects for artists, writers, M=
BAs, lawyers, and even doctors. If Vonnegut&#8217;s right, we&#8217;ll end =
up unemployed, undignified, unsatisfied, unfulfilled. Maybe we&#8217;ll dig=
 some holes, and fill them back in.</span></p><p style=3D"color: #404040; f=
ont-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">But me, I think tha=
t Asimov was more prescient. His vision is kind of already happening now. W=
e&#8217;re just wrapping &#8220;whatever we wish&#8221; in games masqueradi=
ng as jobs.&#160;</p><h3 class=3D"header-with-anchor-widget" style=3D"-moz-=
osx-font-smoothing: subpixel-antialiased; -webkit-font-smoothing: subpixel-=
antialiased; color: #404040; font-family: 'SF Compact Display', -apple-syst=
em, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, '=
Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 1.375em=
; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.16em; margin: 1em 0 0.625em 0; position=
: relative;"><strong>The Present and Far Future of Work</strong></h3><p sty=
le=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px =
0;"><span>We&#8217;re still some years away from computers and robots wipin=
g out the subwork of humanity, so the jury is still out, but I think if Asi=
mov missed something, it&#8217;s that humans are competitive animals who de=
rive meaning from work. Maybe this, too, will change with time, but until t=
housands of years of evolution&#8217;s hard wiring are re-wired, I assume w=
e&#8217;ll want to keep striving towards </span><em>something</em><span>.&#=
160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26=
px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>My guess is that </span><strong>work and gam=
es are going to continue to blend</strong><span>.</span></p><p style=3D"col=
or: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span=
>My most popular essay ever, </span><em><a href=3D"https://substack.com/red=
irect/a3b021d8-2286-4284-8563-4406cdf24a84?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7Gn=
A_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel=3D"" style=3D"color: #404040; text-=
decoration: underline;">The Great Online Game</a><span>,</span></em><span> =
touched on this idea a bit. The internet is like a big, global game with re=
al-world consequences. But what I&#8217;m talking about here is a little di=
fferent.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-=
height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>A couple weeks ago, I was listenin=
g to </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/ec735c50-6745-40c1-890=
9-435184e0000b?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8E=
